<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-9780] Get rid of CFMetaData isPurged(), markPurged()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-9780</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3578&quot; title=&quot;Multithreaded commitlog&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-3578&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-3578&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; added a new &lt;tt&gt;isPurged&lt;/tt&gt; field to &lt;tt&gt;CFMetaData&lt;/tt&gt;. It&apos;s only being used by &lt;tt&gt;CommitLogSegment.markDirty()&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The linked patch removed the field and all the purge-related methods, replacing that condition with &lt;tt&gt;!Schema.instance.hasCF()&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That said, I&apos;m not sure that the check makes sense at all, with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-5202&quot; title=&quot;CFs should have globally and temporally unique CF IDs to prevent &amp;quot;reusing&amp;quot; data from earlier incarnation of same CF name&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-5202&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-5202&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12844422">CASSANDRA-9780</key>
            <summary>Get rid of CFMetaData isPurged(), markPurged()</summary>
