                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14623760" author="iamaleksey" created="Sun, 12 Jul 2015 11:28:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;cassci &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/iamaleksey/job/iamaleksey-9780-testall/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;testall&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/iamaleksey/job/iamaleksey-9780-dtest/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;dtest&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14624432" author="benedict" created="Mon, 13 Jul 2015 09:37:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d prefer we not do concurrent map lookups unnecessarily on critical paths, though it is certainly not a tremendous burden compared to other activities we currently must undertake.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fortunately I think you&apos;re right: this is no longer necessary, as we will not replay for unknown CFs. So let&apos;s just remove it entirely.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14624482" author="iamaleksey" created="Mon, 13 Jul 2015 10:21:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thought so, thanks. Force-pushed the removal to the same branch, cassci is rerunning the tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14624553" author="iamaleksey" created="Mon, 13 Jul 2015 11:41:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;cassci not unhappier than usual. Committed to trunk as &lt;tt&gt;5ba79cbf208649d36ba04834fc8ef242638dee7e&lt;/tt&gt;, thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
